==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: submarine sandwich
<hw>sub`ma*rine" sand"wich</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A large
sandwich on an elongated roll, usually incompletely cut into two halves,
filed with various cold cuts, meatballs, lettuce, cheese, tomatoes,
olives, etc., and spiced variously, and often having oil or other
dressing applied; called also <altname>hoagie</altname>,
<altname>hero</altname>, <altname>hero sandwich</altname>,
<altname>grinder</altname>, <altname>sub</altname>,
<altname>submarine</altname>, <altname>poor boy</altname>, and
<altname>Italian sandwich</altname>. A single such sandwich may
consitute a substantial meal. Very large variants are sometimes prepared
for social gatherings and cut into pieces for individual
consumption.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Submarshal</ent>⟦br⟧
